    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-02T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="489"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.4111/7–254: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 489<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Canada (<persName corresp="#p_STUARTRD1"
                            type="from">Stuart</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-02T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 2, 1954—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. <persName corresp="#p_MCKAYRA1">McKay</persName> on behalf <persName
                        corresp="#p_PEARSONLBM1">Pearson</persName> today briefed us on <persName
                        corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName>–<persName corresp="#p_EDENA1"
                        >Eden</persName> visit,<note n="1" xml:id="d489fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName> visited Ottawa June 29–30.</note>
                    making these points: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Talks mostly report on Washington visit including attitude toward
                            France and <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> which Canada supports.
                                <persName corresp="#p_PEARSONLBM1">Pearson</persName> intends
                            express strong views to French Ambassador here.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Canadians faintly surprised Washington talks produced no agreed
                            program Southeast Asia except working party but <persName
                                corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName> appeared satisfied.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> unexpectedly
                            raised question Moscow visit to <persName corresp="#p_STLAURENTLS1">St.
                                Laurent</persName> who was unprepared but promptly countered with
                            questions as to value such visit unless we had advance assurance Russian
                            willingness negotiate and intention abide by agreements made. <persName
                                corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> had no reply to
                            this.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName> hinted imminent <persName
                                corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> retirement in terms
                            his own need for holiday before assuming greater responsibilities.
                                <persName corresp="#p_PEARSONLBM1">Pearson</persName> predicts
                            around August 1 as probable date retirement.</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>Both <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> and
                                <persName corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName> appeared delighted
                            with Washington visit. <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1"
                                >Churchill</persName> particularly pleased with warmth of welcome at
                            White House and affectionate deference shown him by President. <persName
                                corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName> appears to have developed newly
                            cordial relationship with <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                                >Dulles</persName>.</item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>Briefing of <persName>Heeney</persName> by <persName
                                corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Livy Merchant</persName> greatly
                            appreciated and most valuable.<note n="2" xml:id="d489fn2">
                                <persName corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName> briefed
                                Ambassador <persName>Heeney</persName> on the course of the talks on
                                June 28, reviewing in “fair detail” the European aspects and less
                                thoroughly the discussions on Southeast Asia. (Memorandum of
                                conversation, June 28; 033.4111/6–2854)</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_STUARTRD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
